news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body starts to raze 25 illegal structures
news.para: However, civic activists have demanded that there should be regular monitoring by the municipal staff in all the eight wards so that mushrooming of illegal buildings and structures is nipped in the bud.

news.title: Dehradun smart city projects nears completion, has the city become better?
news.para: Dehradun is the only city in Uttarakhand selected for the Centre’s Smart City initiative in 2017, with a budget exceeding Rs 1,000 crore, funded equally by the Centre and state.

news.title: CVC Capital Partners pips EQT, set to buy Aavas Financiers for Rs 7,000 crore
news.para: Current promoters of the affordable housing finance company, private equity firms Kedaara Capital and Partners Group, are looking to exit their eight-year-old joint investment making a 6x return.

news.title: Two builders face Rs 1.8 crore cheating case in Kalyan
news.para: The Rs 1.8 crore cheating case was registered after flat buyers discovered the alleged fraud and finally approached the Thane Economic Offence Wing (EOW), which in turn directed the local Bazarpeth police to file an FIR.

news.title: Gurgaon One flat owners protest against hike in upkeep fee, defunct lifts
news.para: One of the main grievances voiced by the residents was the persistent problem of water seepage in the basement, which they claimed had caused visible damage to the building's beams and pillars.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body directs contractors to clear construction debris or pay up
news.para: According to the order, contractors must clear debris from ongoing projects and ensure compliance through regular monitoring by officials.

news.title: Signature Global cuts net debt by 16% to Rs 980 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: "The company aims to keep net debt below 0.5 times of the projected operating surplus for the ongoing financial year, as a long term discipline," the presentation said.

news.title: UK: Bellway's revenue dips 31% to $3 billion in year ended July 31
news.para: British homebuilders, hit by a prolonged cost-of-living squeeze, are set to benefit from the first cut in UK interest rates in more than four years. Many UK mortgage lenders cut rates in anticipation of the long-awaited move earlier this month, although the Bank of England played down the prospect of a series of rapid cuts.

news.title: Assam cabinet approves land and space lease management policy 2024
news.para: Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma said that to boost Assam's prospects as a preferred destination for setting up manufacturing base Electronics and Information Technology, the state cabinet has accorded approval to Land and Space Lease Management Policy, 2024 for Information Technology Parks/ Electric Manufacturing Clusters in Assam.

news.title: Only 40% of homestays are registered in Karnataka
news.para: Sources said that homestays have proliferated in the Western Ghats without any restrictions. Some influential individuals have even set up resorts under the guise of homestays.

news.title: Builders in UK boosted by rate cut and promise of planning reforms
news.para: "The UK housebuilding sector is, with one voice, sharing the view that the new Labour government has made a good start in trying to fix the UK's broken housing market," RBC Capital Markets analyst Anthony Codling told Reuters.

news.title: Pune: Glitch in Aadhaar verification system disrupts e-registrations of properties
news.para: The issue has affected e-registration of property documents from developers’ offices as well. The breakdown in online services since August 6 has led to a significant increase in footfall at sub-registrar offices across the state, a registration department official said.

news.title: Berger Paints' net profit dips 0.25% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Berger Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 3,127.34 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 2.77 per cent from Rs 3,043.09 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' net profit dips 86.72% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 350.29 crore in Q1 FY25, a dip of 39.45 per cent from Rs 578.51 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Government to provide assistance of Rs 2.30 lakh crore under PMAY-Urban's second phase
news.para: According to a statement, the government will provide an assistance of Rs 2.30 lakh crore under the scheme. A total of 1.18 crore houses have been sanctioned in the first phase of PMAY-U 2.0, while more than 85.5 lakh houses have already been constructed and delivered to the beneficiaries.

news.title: Canara Bank hikes lending rate by 5 bps across tenors
news.para: ​The benchmark one-year tenor MCLR, which is used to price most consumer loans such as auto and personal, will be at 9 per cent against the earlier rate of 8.95 per cent, Canara Bank said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Kamdhenu's profit grows 28% to over Rs 15 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Kamdhenu's total income reduced to Rs 191.10 crore from Rs 210.45 crore in the first quarter a year ago, the company said in an exchange filing.

news.title: Blackstone sells over 31 crore units in Nexus Select Trust for Rs 4,355 crore
news.para: According to exchange data, Blackstone sold 31.55 crore units in Nexus Select Trust at Rs 138 apiece, taking the total transaction value to Rs 4,354.90 crore.
